Design Team Survey

Jake Rozran

2021-04-08

Design Team Preferences

The design team, overall, prefers doing Design Strategy & Research and Interaction Design, followed closely with People Management. Less favored are Content Design and Visual Design.

This is not to say that these groups are universally liked or not liked. Within each area, there are specific preferences and dislikes.

For example, within a less preferred area, Visual Design, the function of Product Design is highly preferred. On the flip side of this: Within the preferred area of Design Strategy & Research, Qualitative Research is a less preferred area.
